<br>
My grandmother died of cancer... after she had chemo... the chemo killed part of her colon and they didn't notice.  It was scant few days from her going into the hospital to dead.  They didn't want us to come up there because they didn't want us to remember her like that.   Same when my grandfather was dying, they didn't want us to come to the hospital during the last few quick days as all his systems were shutting down.  My grandmother died in '94, my grandfather in '85.  <br>
<br>
My other grandparents were killed in a car accident.  My grandfather had a stroke while driving and crashed, both of them died within a few hours.  My mother said a few days before her mother had said she wanted to go with her husband and not be left alone.  She died about 1 hour after he did.  This was in '79.<br>
<br>
My great grandfather died when I was  7 (in '73).  I still remember the funeral, the Catholic church where the mass was held, and what he looked like in the casket.  <br>
<br>
Death is not easy and I don't think we ever do stop grieving and feeling guilty for not doing or being more.  As much as I have a crappy relationship with my parents... I could not imagine how I would feel if either were to die right now.<br>
<br>
May whatever diety (or lack thereof) you believe in watch over you and guide you in your sorrow.<br>
<br>
As an aside... the movie &quot;Wit&quot; gave me some closure over my grandmother.  It is about a woman dealing with a very advanced form of cancer. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dididaryth>Didi D Aryth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Worshipping Tallonar since 3160</span><br>  Posts: 1125<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/10/03 2:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1648.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Well, there's a first time for everything</span><hr size=1> *hugs Tzaroth*<br>
